{"id":56,"date":"2022-11-23T00:59:43","date_gmt":"2022-11-23T00:59:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/?page_id=56"},"modified":"2026-03-23T04:25:44","modified_gmt":"2026-03-23T04:25:44","slug":"research","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/research\/","title":{"rendered":"Research"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The UW Institute for Neurodiversity and Employment fosters interdisciplinary collaborations among UW scholars and established research collaborations with scholars from other leading research centers with a common focus on neurodiversity employment to:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Investigate effective employment practices and translate them into practice<\/li>\n<li>Investigate education support for employment at critical transition stages<\/li>\n<li>Investigate mental health and behavioral support for employment<\/li>\n<li>Develop and assess assistive technologies<\/li>\n<li>Develop and assess transition and career pathway programming<\/li>\n<li>Collaborate with other neurodiversity research centers around the globe<\/li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\"><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div  class=\"grid row equal   \" >\n<div  class=\"col-sm\">\n<div  class=\"card text-center inset lightgold \" style=\"width:100%\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h2 class=\"card-title\">Featured Project<\/h2>\n<div class=\"card-image-inset\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2026\/03\/Playbook_cover.jpg\" class=\"card-img card-img-inset\" alt=\"cupcakes\"><\/div>\n<p><strong>Autism @ Work and @Neurodiversity at Work Playbooks:<\/strong> Learn from leading employers about how to make workplaces welcoming to neurodivergent employees.<\/p>\n<p class=\"button\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/neurodiversity-at-work-playbook\/\" class=\"btn btn-sm white \"><span>Get the Playbooks<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div  class=\"col-sm\">\n<div  class=\"card text-center inset white \" style=\"width:100%\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h2 class=\"card-title\">Research Conference<\/h2>\n<div class=\"card-image-inset\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2026\/03\/NWRC.jpg\" class=\"card-img card-img-inset\" alt=\"cupcakes\"><\/div>\n<p><strong>Neurodiversity at Work Research Conference:<\/strong> Leading scholars, neurodivergent leaders, and leading neurodiversity employers meet in Seattle June 22-24, 2026.<\/p>\n<p class=\"button\"><a href=\"https:\/\/ndatworkresearch.org\/\" class=\"btn btn-sm primary purple \"><span>Conference Details<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<h2>Active Research Projects<\/h2>\n<h3><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/empowering-neurodivergent-librarians\/\"><span style=\"color: #4b2e83;\">Empowering Neurodivergent Librarians<\/span><\/a><\/h3>\n<p>A University of Washington Information School research team, led by Dr. Hala Annabi, is conducting a two-year research project that aims to improve the capacity of libraries to recruit, onboard, retain, and advance neurodivergent librarians, who currently face barriers to inclusion in library workplaces.<\/p>\n<h2>Publications<\/h2>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #4b2e83;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/neurodiversity-at-work-playbook\/\">Neurodiversity @ Work Playbook Series<\/a><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In their research, Dr. Hala Annabi and her team systematically examined how firms established their neurodiverse employment programs and how they sustain them. The resulting playbooks serve as guides for companies and federal agencies to establish programs of their own.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The UW Institute for Neurodiversity and Employment fosters interdisciplinary collaborations among UW scholars and established research collaborations with scholars from other leading research centers with a common focus on neurodiversity employment to: In